                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Beaupré reports that order has been restored in the city and that business
                    and traffic are approaching normal conditions. The indications are that the
                    government will be able to suppress the uprising without difficulty. Telegrams
                    and the press are controlled by the censor.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
